{
  "stem": "13817.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 14.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In the wintertime, we went-- near the river, to-- to-- the [INAUDIBLE] would flood-- flood with water and then it would freeze over and we would ice skate in there.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But this was just a normal thing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And a big thing was having a bicycle, which everybody had, especially me because I just took it out from the business.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We sold them.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So as a little boy, every time I grew a little bit, a bigger bicycle was there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So this was-- and then naturally like I said, the main entertainment was soccer.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was all day long.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So what happened in '33?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "How did you live?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, in 1933, all of a sudden, everything changed.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The kids which were playing with me all of a sudden didn't say hello to me-- some of them.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Some did.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Some of them, especially one, who went to school with me at the gymnasium, he all of a sudden started not talking to me, making troubles, making slight remarks.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Other boy who played soccer on the same team than I did, for instance, pushed me off the sidewalk and said the Jews have to walk in the street.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "A boy I grew-- my age, we grew up together, and from one week to the other or from one day to the other, he changed.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He put on a big [INAUDIBLE] uniform, and he thought he was-- he was already the king of Germany.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "This is how the things changed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Then in the beginning of '33 after [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Hitler took over, the Jews didn't think he would last for long because every few months there was a different government in Germany at that time because the recession and everything.",
      "word_count": 42
    }
  ],
